@mistercrunch cool, I'll update it after your PR. I think the function approach should allow us to reproduce GKs:

```python
def GET_FEATURE_FLAGS_FUNC(feature_flags_dict):
    if (
        is_admin(g.user) or
        is_data_scientist(g.user) or 
        g.user.id % 10 == 0
    ):
        feature_flags_dict['some_feature'] = True
    return feature_flags_dict
```

My first implementation of this extended the feature flag from a boolean to a dict, but @xtinec suggested separating them. I also have no strong opinions on one vs. the other approach.

